user_reviews.Description:
I recently had a disappointing experience with the SMP service that I cannot recommend. Initially, I was excited based on the consultations and promises made, but unfortunately, the outcome did not match my expectations.

The results were uneven and lacked the realism I was promised. Despite my attempts to communicate my concerns, I was assured that my results would look natural with my hair length (a 1-2, short but not shaved). However, after two sessions, it became clear that it would only look natural with a shaved head. My feedback was not taken seriously, and little effort was made to rectify the situation in a timely manner. I had a formal event two weeks later and was told my SMP would be undetectable by then, but that wasn't the case. I was advised to use hair fibers as a solution instead.

The lack of support and communication left me feeling disheartened, especially after investing time and money. A service should stand by its results, particularly when they are permanent, and in this case, it did not.

I urge others to carefully consider their options before committing to this SMP service, as no one deserves to feel self-conscious or embarrassed about their appearance. Thankfully, I was able to get a partial refund, but the pricing for this service is steep for the results I received. Every knowledgeable source I've spoken to has agreed that my experience with this practitioner was borderline unethical. Time to explore laser options..

I recently had a disappointing experience with the SMP service that I cannot recommend. Initially, I was excited based on the consultations and promises made, but unfortunately, the outcome did not match my expectations.

The results were uneven and lacked the realism I was promised. Despite my attempts to communicate my concerns, I was assured that my results would look natural with my hair length (a 1-2, short but not shaved). However, after two sessions, it became clear that it would only look natural with a shaved head. My feedback was not taken seriously, and little effort was made to rectify the situation in a timely manner. I had a formal event two weeks later and was told my SMP would be undetectable by then, but that wasn't the case. I was advised to use hair fibers as a solution instead.

The lack of support and communication left me feeling disheartened, especially after investing time and money. A service should stand by its results, particularly when they are permanent, and in this case, it did not.

I urge others to carefully consider their options before committing to this SMP service, as no one deserves to feel self-conscious or embarrassed about their appearance. Thankfully, I was able to get a partial refund, but the pricing for this service is steep for the results I received. Every knowledgeable source I've spoken to has agreed that my experience with this practitioner was borderline unethical. Time to explore laser options..

user_reviews.Description:
I was in town for the day and needed a clean up. Found this place and met Stoney and the gang. Only had to wait about 15 minutes before I got in the chair. Juan was my barber. I asked for a tight fade with a dark top. That is basically what I got and was decently satisfied with the results. With that being said, I was not satisfied with the haircut process itself. Juan's technique was jabby and harsh. I often felt the clippers hit directly against my skin before trimming, leaving rough patches of bluntly cut hair and was abrasive on my skin. He trimmed under my neck without much care causing bad razor burn and uneven texture. My hair is fairly soft and I have had really smooth fades but this fade turned out choppier likely due to the quick flick technique he used.

I had the opportunity to watch Stoney cut a few clients and his technique was much smoother, with really clean lines and the guys came out sharp without too much irritation, from what I could tell. Juan was also distracted by his phone during the cut, which I understand happens when you're working all day, but I think that affected his overall performance.

In photos the pinkish areas are where I experienced the most discomfort from clipper burn. My under neck hurt the most. I trim my neck with my own electric trimmer and have never been scratched up like that. I use witch hazel, shea butter, and aloe vera to help the healing process. I plan to use a light salt or sugar scrub over the next few days to help soften the hair to prevent in-grown hairs and further irritation.

Overall, the cut turned out alright and $30 wasn't too bad given it's DC, though I have had cleaner for less. The guys were really cool and I appreciate a Black owned barbershop doing their best, but I would recommend tightening up the practice with more consideration of skin and hair textures for even better results.
